Students passed the course should know classification of fractures and methods of conservative and operative treatment, diagnostics and treatment of orthopaedic diseases and polytrauma patients. Explanations are given about indications and treatment results in different surgical treatment options like: arthroscopy, osteosynthesis, arthroplasty, spinal fusions. At least one practical study will be held in policlinic with consultant and one in trauma emergency. Walk arounds in trauma department, investigation of patients and presentation. Every student should prepare patient case with theoretic analysis and present it one of last seminars.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give deeper knowledge of diagnostics, treatment and prophylaxis of musculoskeletal injuries and orthopaedic diseases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student, passed course: -	knows investigation of skeletal system -	understands principles of treatment of different orthopaedic conditions -	understands principles of treatment of injuries of skeletal system -	knows principles of physiotherapy in case of orthopaedic conditions and traumas -	understands critical situations and subsequently urgency in treatment connected to traumas and orthopaedic diseases
